The paper discusses the Book Citation Index and Science Citation Index, which are databases used in bibliometrics and information science. The paper also explores the citation impact of books, book chapters, and edited volumes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) which deals with the organization, retrieval, and distribution of digital information. The paper also discusses information retrieval (IR) and citation analysis, which are sub-fields of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper touches on cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social media (cs.SI) in relation to bibliometrics and information science.
